  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age 18 or older

          -  Current daily smoking defined as smoking ≥5 cigarettes per day and having smoked for
             at least 3 months. During the first visit smoking status will be verified by a Carbon
             Monoxide level of at least 8 parts per million.

          -  Have a mobile phone and use text messaging at least monthly

          -  Be planning to quit smoking without pharmacological help.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Significant cognitive impairment

          -  Current therapy or pharmacological intervention for smoking or nicotine cravings

          -  Inability to read English
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
